    "body": "We at SFT-SPI would like to use libc's implementation of iconv, as opposed to libiconv one. This PR introduces a new virtual package `iconv` and a dummy package `libc` to provide it. \r\n\r\nlib's and libiconv's implementation of iconv should be compatible on API level, but I'm testing this just in case.\r\n\r\nPackages that directly depend on libiconv:\r\n- [x] apr-util\r\n- [x] dcmtk\r\n- [x] doxygen\r\n- [x] gdal\r\n- [x] glib\r\n- [x] gnuplot\r\n- [x] gtksourceview\r\n- [x] libgd\r\n- [x] libunistring\r\n- [x] libxslt\r\n- [x] ncl\r\n- [x] procps\r\n- [x] unixodbc\r\n- [x] xerces-c\r\n- [x] bash\r\n- [x] diffutils\r\n- [x] gcc\r\n- [x] git\r\n- [x] gnupg\r\n- [x] grass\r\n- [x] lftp\r\n- [x] libspatialite\r\n- [x] libxml2\r\n- [x] mono\r\n- [x] poppler\r\n- [x] tar\r\n- [x] wget\r\n",
